author: Janet Hook
title: Obama Approval Rating Finishes Strong but Falls Short of Reagan, Clinton - Washington Wire - WSJ
text:
President Barack Obama is ending his two terms in the White House on a high note — but not as high as some of his predecessors. A new Wall Street Journal/NBC News poll out Tuesday found that 56% of Americans approve of the job Mr. Obama has done as president. That is the highest level […]
